1
00:00:06,896 --> 00:00:08,646
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:10,937 --> 00:00:13,437
[tense music playing]

3
00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:55,437
[horns honking]

4
00:01:15,187 --> 00:01:17,187
[driver] Aren't you getting
a little bit too old for him?

5
00:01:17,271 --> 00:01:19,187
No, this is my friend.

6
00:01:19,271 --> 00:01:20,354
[driver] Your friend?

7
00:01:21,104 --> 00:01:22,437
[in Zulu] You know, Mandla…

8
00:01:24,521 --> 00:01:25,604
[sighs]

9
00:01:31,271 --> 00:01:32,812
[horns honking]

10
00:01:34,271 --> 00:01:36,396
[in English] I need to take you home,
feed you, and take you to cricket.

11
00:01:36,479 --> 00:01:37,687
[in Xhosa] Looks like we're gonna be late.

12
00:01:37,771 --> 00:01:38,771
[in English] Good.

13
00:01:40,604 --> 00:01:41,896
Are they still bullying you?

14
00:01:43,062 --> 00:01:44,062
Yeah.

15
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:45,229
Mandla, what did I say to you last time?

16
00:01:45,312 --> 00:01:47,271
-Stand up to them.
-[in Xhosa] So why didn't you?

17
00:01:47,354 --> 00:01:49,854
'Cause they're gonna carry on doing
what they're doing if you don't do that.

18
00:01:49,937 --> 00:01:51,312
But they're much bigger than me.

19
00:01:51,396 --> 00:01:53,521
-Did you tell Coach?
-Yeah.

20
00:01:53,604 --> 00:01:54,729
And what did she say?

21
00:01:54,812 --> 00:01:57,187
I should stop being a crybaby.

22
00:01:57,271 --> 00:01:59,187
I'm gonna talk
to this little coach of yours.

23
00:01:59,271 --> 00:02:01,604
It's okay, Dad. It's just one sandwich.

24
00:02:01,687 --> 00:02:03,562
I gave them one, and I have one.

25
00:02:03,646 --> 00:02:04,646
[laughs]

26
00:02:04,729 --> 00:02:05,979
-[gunshot]
-[gasps]

27
00:02:07,146 --> 00:02:09,354
[people screaming]

28
00:02:10,021 --> 00:02:11,021
[Mandla] Dad.

29
00:02:17,104 --> 00:02:18,729
It's gonna be okay, my boy. All right?

30
00:02:18,812 --> 00:02:20,562
-Dad.
-It's okay, it's okay, it's okay.

31
00:02:23,104 --> 00:02:24,104
Dad!

32
00:02:24,812 --> 00:02:26,021
I'm scared.

33
00:02:26,854 --> 00:02:28,146
It's gonna be fine.

34
00:02:29,104 --> 00:02:30,104
[in Zulu] Hey, you!

35
00:02:30,687 --> 00:02:32,562
[in Afrikaans] Hey, Sarafina, out!

36
00:02:32,646 --> 00:02:34,521
Get out the fucking car, man!

37
00:02:34,604 --> 00:02:35,771
Get out of the car, man.

38
00:02:35,854 --> 00:02:38,354
[in Xhosa] I'm begging you, my brother.
I have a child in the back, please.

39
00:02:39,979 --> 00:02:41,312
[thug 1] Oh…

40
00:02:41,396 --> 00:02:42,687
Sorry.

41
00:02:42,771 --> 00:02:44,562
[in Tswana] He's got a crèche in the back.

42
00:02:45,187 --> 00:02:46,271
Hello, boy.

43
00:02:46,354 --> 00:02:47,437
[thug 2] Hello, boy.

44
00:02:47,521 --> 00:02:49,187
Papa is gonna be fine, okay?

45
00:02:49,271 --> 00:02:50,812
Why are you looking at me
like that, asshole?

46
00:02:50,896 --> 00:02:52,187
I'll blow your head off.

47
00:02:53,229 --> 00:02:54,687
I'll blow your head off, man.

48
00:02:55,896 --> 00:02:58,521
[in Afrikaans] Calm down. Calm down.

49
00:02:59,271 --> 00:03:00,271
[clicks tongue]

50
00:03:02,354 --> 00:03:03,562
-Hey, you. Piss off.
-Piss off!

51
00:03:03,646 --> 00:03:04,687
-Piss off.
-Piss off.

52
00:03:04,771 --> 00:03:07,187
-Get out of the fucking car, man.
-[passenger screaming]

53
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:09,104
[thug 2] Hey, man…

54
00:03:09,187 --> 00:03:10,312
[engine starts]

55
00:03:10,396 --> 00:03:12,479
-No, man, Spyker, you always--
-Don't talk shit.

56
00:03:17,479 --> 00:03:18,687
[breathes deeply]

57
00:03:28,771 --> 00:03:30,062
[employee groans]

58
00:03:30,146 --> 00:03:34,062
[employee, in Sotho] Boss, it was nothing.
We were just chilling with the guys.

59
00:03:34,146 --> 00:03:36,896
It was just a conversation
over a few beers.

60
00:03:36,979 --> 00:03:39,354
Then he asked me
where you were and who you were with.

61
00:03:39,437 --> 00:03:40,771
I would never put you in danger.

62
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:42,396
I would never do that.

63
00:03:43,021 --> 00:03:44,937
[Eezy] Then why were they looking for you?

64
00:03:45,021 --> 00:03:48,729
Boss, I was broke and needed some money.

65
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:51,937
So you think it was nothing

66
00:03:53,104 --> 00:03:56,812
that his boss, Rolo, wants to kill me?

67
00:03:56,896 --> 00:03:59,687
And you told his driver
exactly where I am,

68
00:03:59,771 --> 00:04:02,562
who I'm with and what we're doing.
Is that nothing?

69
00:04:02,646 --> 00:04:04,146
Please forgive me, my boss.

70
00:04:04,229 --> 00:04:05,896
I made a mistake, boss.

71
00:04:05,979 --> 00:04:08,312
Boss, I'm begging you. I need this job.

72
00:04:09,146 --> 00:04:10,729
I'm begging you, boss.

73
00:04:10,812 --> 00:04:12,312
-Okay.
-Please forgive me.

74
00:04:14,521 --> 00:04:15,937
Okay.

75
00:04:16,021 --> 00:04:18,187
-I'll do you a favor, boy. You hear me?
-Yes, boss.

76
00:04:22,104 --> 00:04:23,396
We're going to put you up there.

77
00:04:24,437 --> 00:04:26,437
-You see the top of that car?
-Yes, my boss.

78
00:04:26,521 --> 00:04:27,812
That's your new position.

79
00:04:28,437 --> 00:04:31,021
I'm giving you a view of everything

80
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,146
that's happening in the scrap yard.
Understood?

81
00:04:33,229 --> 00:04:34,979
-Don't mess up.
-Oh, boss.

82
00:04:35,062 --> 00:04:36,521
Thank you so much, boss.

83
00:04:36,604 --> 00:04:38,396
You've helped me so much.
I don't even know what to say.

84
00:04:38,479 --> 00:04:39,521
Thank you so much, boss.

85
00:04:39,604 --> 00:04:41,229
-[gun cocks]
-[gunshot]

86
00:04:41,312 --> 00:04:42,437
[body thuds]

87
00:04:49,896 --> 00:04:50,896
[in English] And then?

88
00:05:04,271 --> 00:05:06,229
-Hi, my beautiful boy.
-[Mandla] Hi!

89
00:05:06,312 --> 00:05:07,312
Hi, Mom.

90
00:05:07,396 --> 00:05:09,396
Hello, my handsome. How're you doing?

91
00:05:09,479 --> 00:05:10,854
-I'm good.
-Good.

92
00:05:10,937 --> 00:05:11,979
How was school?

93
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:14,729
Um, there were these two guys with guns.

94
00:05:14,812 --> 00:05:17,437
Um, they pointed the gun right at Daddy.

95
00:05:17,521 --> 00:05:19,437
And there was a lady screaming.

96
00:05:20,896 --> 00:05:21,896
[Mom] What?

97
00:05:21,979 --> 00:05:23,062
It was nothing.

98
00:05:24,896 --> 00:05:26,187
Are you okay?

99
00:05:26,271 --> 00:05:27,312
Mm-hmm?

100
00:05:27,396 --> 00:05:28,812
Okay. Eat up.

101
00:05:30,854 --> 00:05:32,062
What happened?

102
00:05:32,146 --> 00:05:34,354
It was a hit.
[in Xhosa] Portia, it was broad daylight.

103
00:05:34,437 --> 00:05:37,187
Those guys were casual, no rush, walking
around without a care in the world.

104
00:05:37,271 --> 00:05:39,187
They looked at each other,
then they looked at this one,

105
00:05:39,271 --> 00:05:41,021
as if they were thinking of something.

106
00:05:41,771 --> 00:05:43,437
[in Zulu] Maybe he should stay home then.

107
00:05:43,521 --> 00:05:44,937
[in English] No. No, no, no.

108
00:05:45,021 --> 00:05:46,271
Zak, are you sure?

109
00:05:46,854 --> 00:05:48,771
He'll be fine. I promise you.

110
00:05:51,979 --> 00:05:52,979
All right.

111
00:05:53,896 --> 00:05:55,479
-[Zak growling]
-[Mandla giggling]

112
00:05:56,104 --> 00:05:57,562
Go get your bag. Go and get ready.

113
00:05:57,646 --> 00:05:59,854
[growls] Come, come, come.

114
00:05:59,937 --> 00:06:02,021
[Portia] Mandla, go wash your hands.

115
00:06:05,312 --> 00:06:06,521
You sure you're okay?

116
00:06:07,229 --> 00:06:08,979
[sighs] Yeah, I'm fine.

117
00:06:10,146 --> 00:06:11,354
It's okay if you're not.

118
00:06:14,187 --> 00:06:16,396
[Zak, in Xhosa]
Damn, what smells like that, Brother?

119
00:06:18,021 --> 00:06:19,146
It smells.

120
00:06:19,229 --> 00:06:20,521
-Yes.
-It smells.

121
00:06:22,354 --> 00:06:24,104
-Jesus!
-Can you smell it?

122
00:06:24,187 --> 00:06:25,646
Where did you get this?
At Mandela Village?

123
00:06:25,729 --> 00:06:28,146
I got it from Stivovo, my friend.

124
00:06:29,104 --> 00:06:30,396
-Stivovo?
-Yes.

125
00:06:30,979 --> 00:06:32,354
[Zak] Just throw it away, Brother.

126
00:06:32,437 --> 00:06:33,729
-It's not good enough for this kitchen.
-No.

127
00:06:33,812 --> 00:06:35,229
Dude, I can't throw it away.

128
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:37,771
He sold it to me at a cheap price.
It was a bargain.

129
00:06:37,854 --> 00:06:38,854
-A bargain?
-Yeah.

130
00:06:38,937 --> 00:06:39,979
-A bargain for this?
-Yeah.

131
00:06:40,062 --> 00:06:43,021
It's off and smells like it wasn't put
in the fridge after coming off the truck.

132
00:06:43,104 --> 00:06:45,271
No, he has a fridge,
but it's not big enough.

133
00:06:45,854 --> 00:06:48,479
I'm just trying this out.
Why are you being so harsh?

134
00:06:48,562 --> 00:06:49,604
Gosh.

135
00:06:50,312 --> 00:06:51,437
No, man.

136
00:06:56,312 --> 00:06:57,562
Thanks, thanks, my brother.

137
00:06:57,646 --> 00:06:59,062
Hey, leave my order, man.

138
00:06:59,146 --> 00:07:00,687
-Yeah, yeah, I know…
-What's wrong with you?

139
00:07:00,771 --> 00:07:02,062
…why are you shouting?

140
00:07:02,146 --> 00:07:04,021
-Do you want a burger?
-Thank you, boss.

141
00:07:04,104 --> 00:07:06,854
Listen, tell my nephew
he's got a shitty dad.

142
00:07:06,937 --> 00:07:08,812
-Boss, please may I have fifty rand?
-Piss off.

143
00:07:08,896 --> 00:07:10,437
-[person] As old as I am?
-[Brother] Whatever.

144
00:07:16,687 --> 00:07:18,271
[equipment whirring]

145
00:07:28,521 --> 00:07:30,271
[in Sotho] I'm going to need
another driver.

146
00:07:34,354 --> 00:07:35,562
Karwas?

147
00:07:38,812 --> 00:07:40,646
[Eezy] Does he know how to drive well?

148
00:07:43,854 --> 00:07:45,562
Okay, go with him for today.

149
00:07:46,604 --> 00:07:49,021
Teach him how to drive
and show him the ropes.

150
00:07:49,812 --> 00:07:51,646
But I need to be with you, boss.

151
00:07:52,771 --> 00:07:54,187
No, I'll be okay.

152
00:07:56,062 --> 00:07:57,896
It's one day, don't worry about me.

153
00:08:00,812 --> 00:08:01,937
[employee 2 whistles]

154
00:08:02,729 --> 00:08:03,729
Hey!

155
00:08:04,396 --> 00:08:07,562
[in Tswana]
Uh, take that bucket and put it there.

156
00:08:07,646 --> 00:08:09,646
Be quick, hurry up.

157
00:08:18,146 --> 00:08:20,687
-You know how to drive, right?
-Yes.

158
00:08:20,771 --> 00:08:22,646
-Yes, let's go. Step on the clutch.
-Yeah.

159
00:08:22,729 --> 00:08:26,312
Step on the brake,
start the car, and do your thing.

160
00:08:26,396 --> 00:08:29,146
Don't be intimidated
by people on the road, just drive.

161
00:08:29,229 --> 00:08:30,771
-[engine starts]
-Let's go! Go!

162
00:08:31,687 --> 00:08:32,771
Go! Let's go.

163
00:08:32,854 --> 00:08:33,896
[engine revs]

164
00:08:33,979 --> 00:08:35,229
No, no, no!

165
00:08:35,312 --> 00:08:38,146
Push in the clutch.
Yes, that's it, go, go!

166
00:08:38,812 --> 00:08:42,437
No, man. Drive the car, drive the car.

167
00:08:43,146 --> 00:08:44,854
What? What are you doing?

168
00:08:55,896 --> 00:08:56,979
[softly] Go on.

169
00:08:59,562 --> 00:09:01,479
[in Zulu] Yeah. There you go.

170
00:09:02,187 --> 00:09:04,187
[in English] My man, what's the holdup?

171
00:09:06,729 --> 00:09:09,146
-Good morning.
-Yeah, good morning. What's the holdup?

172
00:09:09,771 --> 00:09:11,896
[in Zulu] My brother, it's tea time.

173
00:09:11,979 --> 00:09:14,062
At this time? Guys, y'all aren't serious.

174
00:09:15,146 --> 00:09:16,437
Piss off.

175
00:09:16,521 --> 00:09:17,562
What did you say?

176
00:09:17,646 --> 00:09:18,646
I said piss off.

177
00:09:18,729 --> 00:09:20,854
[phone buzzes]

178
00:09:24,479 --> 00:09:25,521
[in English] Hello?

179
00:09:26,979 --> 00:09:27,979
What?

180
00:09:29,312 --> 00:09:31,146
Yeah, okay. I'm on my way. I'm on my way.

181
00:09:31,229 --> 00:09:32,979
[Mandla sobbing]

182
00:09:34,729 --> 00:09:35,854
Mandla.

183
00:09:36,646 --> 00:09:37,729
Where are they?

184
00:09:44,396 --> 00:09:46,812
[in Xhosa] What's wrong with you guys?
Don't your parents feed you?

185
00:09:46,896 --> 00:09:49,312
[in English] If you ever
touch my son again,

186
00:09:49,396 --> 00:09:51,187
I will go to the cops and I'll report you.

187
00:09:51,271 --> 00:09:54,021
And let me tell you something,
there's no sandwiches or cakes in prison.

188
00:09:54,104 --> 00:09:55,354
-Are we clear?
-Mr. Sikow?

189
00:09:55,437 --> 00:09:56,979
It's Mr. Sigcawu to you.

190
00:09:57,062 --> 00:09:58,854
-This is entirely inappropriate.
-Inappropriate?

191
00:09:58,937 --> 00:10:01,146
Is my son being bullied
and stolen from appropriate?

192
00:10:01,812 --> 00:10:03,729
[in Xhosa] Don't tell me that.

193
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:04,937
[in English] Bullying and theft,

194
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:06,979
and your "appropriate" answer
is to call my son a crybaby?

195
00:10:07,562 --> 00:10:10,437
And these bullies tore off his button,
so you better find it.

196
00:10:10,521 --> 00:10:11,729
Appropriate, my ass.

197
00:10:15,146 --> 00:10:16,146
[clicks tongue]

198
00:10:19,021 --> 00:10:22,187
Dad, were you really
going to call the cops?

199
00:10:22,812 --> 00:10:24,854
[laughs] No, my boy.

200
00:10:24,937 --> 00:10:26,271
[in Xhosa] I just wanted to scare them.

201
00:10:26,354 --> 00:10:27,687
[laughs]

202
00:10:30,312 --> 00:10:31,771
[in English] I still got a sandwich.

203
00:10:31,854 --> 00:10:33,104
Would you like half?

204
00:10:35,229 --> 00:10:36,229
No, I'm fine, my boy.

205
00:10:36,312 --> 00:10:38,396
Thank you very much.
You're so kind, you know.

206
00:10:41,979 --> 00:10:43,646
-[in Xhosa] Look at this rubbish, hey!
-[horn honks]

207
00:10:51,271 --> 00:10:52,437
[in English] Mandla, are you okay?

208
00:10:52,521 --> 00:10:53,646
You sure you're okay?

209
00:10:57,979 --> 00:10:59,979
[in Tswana] Hey, you!
What the fuck are you doing?

210
00:11:00,062 --> 00:11:02,896
-[in Xhosa] Hey, what are you saying?
-I'm saying your driving is shit!

211
00:11:03,604 --> 00:11:05,729
-[in English] Dad, please don't get out.
-[in Tswana] Hey, man!

212
00:11:05,812 --> 00:11:09,396
What kind of rubbish driving is this?
Come here, I want you close.

213
00:11:09,479 --> 00:11:11,604
I want this guy to come closer.
I want him here.

214
00:11:11,687 --> 00:11:13,271
I want to show him something.

215
00:11:13,354 --> 00:11:15,312
Are you high?
Didn't you see the light was red?

216
00:11:15,396 --> 00:11:16,979
I'm sorry. I was the one who--

217
00:11:17,062 --> 00:11:18,771
Zip this mouth of yours.

218
00:11:19,854 --> 00:11:21,229
What kind of driver are you,
passing red lights?

219
00:11:21,312 --> 00:11:23,271
You're the one who drove
past a red light. Are you high?

220
00:11:23,354 --> 00:11:25,479
Hey, this is South Africa.
Where are you rushing to?

221
00:11:25,562 --> 00:11:27,937
You're talking bullshit. Everyone saw you.
Are you stupid or what?

222
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:29,646
I'll grab you with one ball.

223
00:11:29,729 --> 00:11:32,354
With your small, puppy penis.

224
00:11:32,437 --> 00:11:33,854
-Piss off!
-[Zak] You piss off.

225
00:11:33,937 --> 00:11:36,396
-Piss off!
-Hey, you, I'll show you your mother!

226
00:11:36,479 --> 00:11:37,521
Karwas, leave me alone.

227
00:11:37,604 --> 00:11:38,771
-I'm killing this boy.
-Uh-uh, whoa.

228
00:11:38,854 --> 00:11:40,146
-Stop pointing at me.
-I'll kill you.

229
00:11:40,229 --> 00:11:41,312
[Zak] Piss off, man.

230
00:11:41,396 --> 00:11:43,646
Hey, hey, hey. What's wrong with you?

231
00:11:43,729 --> 00:11:46,021
My problem is that you think the rules
don't apply to you. You know that?

232
00:11:46,104 --> 00:11:49,396
[employee 3] My man, you can't tell us
how to drive. Fuck off.

233
00:11:49,479 --> 00:11:50,479
[Zak] Fuck off for what?

234
00:11:50,562 --> 00:11:52,771
[huffing]

235
00:11:52,854 --> 00:11:55,146
[phone buzzing]

236
00:11:57,812 --> 00:11:59,687
[Mandla on phone] Mom, come quick.

237
00:11:59,771 --> 00:12:02,187
Dad's fighting. They're going to hurt him.

238
00:12:02,771 --> 00:12:04,146
[employee 3] Hey, fuck off.

239
00:12:04,229 --> 00:12:05,937
You're not a traffic officer,
you can't tell us how to drive.

240
00:12:06,021 --> 00:12:08,271
You can't drive however
you want to drive. What do you want?

241
00:12:08,354 --> 00:12:11,354
My brother, look,
please go back to your child.

242
00:12:11,437 --> 00:12:13,646
-I'm begging you. Please go back there.
-Wait a minute.

243
00:12:15,812 --> 00:12:17,229
[employee 2] Karwas,
this guy is provoking me.

244
00:12:21,521 --> 00:12:24,062
You're a coward, man. You cow.

245
00:12:24,146 --> 00:12:26,062
Moo!

246
00:12:26,146 --> 00:12:27,896
You're a coward, man.

247
00:12:28,562 --> 00:12:30,396
I'm telling you, I'm saying run.

248
00:12:30,479 --> 00:12:33,062
-[Karwas] Let him go.
-Watch your mouth when you talk to me.

249
00:12:33,146 --> 00:12:34,229
Do you know who I am?

250
00:12:34,312 --> 00:12:37,354
I'm the last man standing, my boy.

251
00:12:37,437 --> 00:12:39,604
Ask about me in the hood.

252
00:12:39,687 --> 00:12:41,562
-Nobody talks to me like that.
-No, man. Leave him alone.

253
00:12:41,646 --> 00:12:43,479
[Zak] Listen here, I know
exactly who I'm talking to.

254
00:12:43,562 --> 00:12:45,062
-Let me bite you.
-[Zak] I know who I'm talking to.

255
00:12:45,146 --> 00:12:46,979
-What are you gonna do?
-Let me show you.

256
00:12:47,062 --> 00:12:48,729
[crowd clamoring]

257
00:12:48,812 --> 00:12:50,521
-Hey!
-Hey, you!

258
00:12:50,604 --> 00:12:52,479
[employee 3] What are you doing?
You're full of shit.

259
00:12:52,562 --> 00:12:56,771
-Bloody shit, bloody fucking dog.
-[in English] Stop!

260
00:13:00,562 --> 00:13:02,854
-Stop!
-Hey! Hey!

261
00:13:04,229 --> 00:13:05,646
-Dog!
-[employee 3] Satan!

262
00:13:05,729 --> 00:13:07,187
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

263
00:13:07,271 --> 00:13:08,729
Dude, please leave.

264
00:13:08,812 --> 00:13:10,271
-[employee 2] Listen, Shoes.
-Please let him go.

265
00:13:10,354 --> 00:13:11,562
-Listen, Shoes.
-Dad!

266
00:13:12,187 --> 00:13:13,229
[employee 2] Listen, Shoes.

267
00:13:13,312 --> 00:13:14,979
-[Mandla] Dad!
-[employee 3] You're terrible, man.

268
00:13:15,062 --> 00:13:16,729
-[Mandla] Dad!
-[Karwas] Please leave him.

269
00:13:16,812 --> 00:13:18,312
Please let him go.

270
00:13:23,437 --> 00:13:25,062
[in Tswana] You're dead, dog.

271
00:13:25,146 --> 00:13:26,437
[crowd gasps]

272
00:13:28,521 --> 00:13:29,562
[in Zulu] Calm down, boy.

273
00:13:29,646 --> 00:13:30,937
[in Afrikaans] Leave me alone.

274
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:34,604
[Karwas] No, man.

275
00:13:38,437 --> 00:13:39,437
Hey!

276
00:13:39,521 --> 00:13:40,979
-[gunshot]
-[people screaming]

277
00:13:41,062 --> 00:13:42,104
[employee 2] Get off me.

278
00:13:42,729 --> 00:13:43,979
[employee 3] Get off me, you 20 kg.

279
00:13:44,062 --> 00:13:45,437
Dude, let's go.

280
00:13:45,521 --> 00:13:47,271
-[Karwas] Lerumo!
-What have you done?

281
00:13:48,062 --> 00:13:49,146
[Lerumo] Let's go.

282
00:13:50,896 --> 00:13:52,521
[distorted] Man, bring my gun.

283
00:13:58,062 --> 00:13:59,146
[employee 3] Let's go.

284
00:14:00,271 --> 00:14:01,562
Mandla.

285
00:14:01,646 --> 00:14:02,854
Mandla. Mandla.

286
00:14:03,896 --> 00:14:04,896
Mandla.

287
00:14:10,604 --> 00:14:11,604
Mandla.

288
00:14:14,646 --> 00:14:17,479
[melancholy music plays]

289
00:14:24,354 --> 00:14:26,562
[Portia exhaling]

290
00:14:48,396 --> 00:14:50,021
[no audible dialogue]

291
00:15:01,729 --> 00:15:04,146
[hip-hop music playing on car stereo]

292
00:15:11,229 --> 00:15:12,521
[in Sotho] So you left that boy there?

293
00:15:13,312 --> 00:15:14,854
[in Tswana] His mouth is shut.
He won't say anything.

294
00:15:14,937 --> 00:15:18,812
How do you know, though? Lerumo?
You're stupid, my man.

295
00:15:18,896 --> 00:15:20,521
That guy is the one who provoked me.

296
00:15:21,187 --> 00:15:24,062
He passed a red light,
and I had to defend myself.

297
00:15:24,146 --> 00:15:26,187
That guy's crazy.
The weed he smokes is killing him.

298
00:15:26,271 --> 00:15:28,271
-Which boy, that little one?
-No, the one with a six-pack.

299
00:15:28,354 --> 00:15:29,604
He was acting like a tough guy.

300
00:15:29,687 --> 00:15:33,437
-He got out of his car and manhandled me.
-[knocking on door]

301
00:15:33,521 --> 00:15:34,604
-Goodness.
-[door opens]

302
00:15:36,979 --> 00:15:37,979
Hello.

303
00:15:38,521 --> 00:15:40,187
Hey, Mr. Eezy does it.

304
00:15:57,354 --> 00:15:58,771
[chuckles]

305
00:15:58,854 --> 00:16:00,312
[thug 1] This money isn't enough.

306
00:16:00,396 --> 00:16:02,562
-I don't have money.
-You don't have money? How?

307
00:16:02,646 --> 00:16:06,062
You own taxis, you dress well,
while I'm struggling.

308
00:16:06,146 --> 00:16:08,396
-What do you have to say about that?
-Young man, lower your voice.

309
00:16:08,479 --> 00:16:11,437
An elder speaks once
and doesn't repeat themselves.

310
00:16:11,521 --> 00:16:13,437
Elders, work is work.

311
00:16:13,521 --> 00:16:15,271
You all know work is work.

312
00:16:15,354 --> 00:16:17,021
Come again. What did you say?

313
00:16:18,021 --> 00:16:19,104
What did you say?

314
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:20,937
Repeat yourself.

315
00:16:22,562 --> 00:16:24,104
With your small beard.

316
00:16:25,229 --> 00:16:26,437
Get out of this place.

317
00:16:28,271 --> 00:16:29,354
Get out.

318
00:16:29,937 --> 00:16:33,979
You busy arguing with my boss?
The big boss?

319
00:16:36,062 --> 00:16:37,146
[Spyker] Let's go.

320
00:16:38,354 --> 00:16:39,354
[door closes]

321
00:16:40,021 --> 00:16:42,437
[heart monitor beeping]

322
00:16:53,229 --> 00:16:54,271
[in Xhosa] My love.

323
00:16:54,854 --> 00:16:56,437
I didn't do this.

324
00:16:57,729 --> 00:16:59,937
Some men ran a red light.

325
00:17:03,604 --> 00:17:05,312
[in English] You always have to be right.

326
00:17:13,646 --> 00:17:14,979
This isn't right.

327
00:17:28,104 --> 00:17:30,771
[in Sotho] So you work
for Ezekiel Rampedi, correct?

328
00:17:32,479 --> 00:17:33,521
Yes.

329
00:17:34,646 --> 00:17:36,437
The machine can't hear silent language.

330
00:17:37,271 --> 00:17:39,187
The recorder isn't picking up your voice.

331
00:17:40,479 --> 00:17:41,479
Oh.

332
00:17:42,229 --> 00:17:43,396
Yes.

333
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,229
So, you were the one driving the vehicle?

334
00:17:46,771 --> 00:17:48,937
-Yes.
-Who was the man driving with you?

335
00:17:51,229 --> 00:17:53,437
Uh, I… I… I don't know him.

336
00:17:53,521 --> 00:17:55,312
-[in English] You don't know?
-I… I don't… I don't kn--

337
00:17:55,396 --> 00:17:57,396
[in English] The man with the gun
in the sporty hat

338
00:17:57,479 --> 00:17:59,271
called the driver of the taxi "Karwas."

339
00:17:59,354 --> 00:18:01,271
That's your name. Right, Karwas?

340
00:18:02,104 --> 00:18:04,312
[in Sotho] My name is Kwanele.

341
00:18:04,937 --> 00:18:07,437
[in English] Oh, Kwanele,
but that's what they call you, right?

342
00:18:07,521 --> 00:18:08,521
Karwas.

343
00:18:09,104 --> 00:18:12,187
[in Sotho] Yes, I wash the taxis at…

344
00:18:12,271 --> 00:18:14,062
-[in English] Is that a "yes"?
-Is that a "yes"?

345
00:18:17,771 --> 00:18:20,062
[in Sotho] May I ask,
how's the little boy?

346
00:18:22,729 --> 00:18:23,937
[in Sotho] He's alive.

347
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,187
He's in ICU.

348
00:18:27,187 --> 00:18:28,229
Who's this?

349
00:18:32,104 --> 00:18:33,396
I don't know him.

350
00:18:34,062 --> 00:18:35,437
[in English]
But he jumped out of your taxi.

351
00:18:35,521 --> 00:18:37,812
And he was sitting right next to you.
And he called you by your name.

352
00:18:37,896 --> 00:18:39,437
You don't know, Kwanele?

353
00:18:41,146 --> 00:18:43,229
[in Sotho] I don't know every passenger
who gets into the taxi.

354
00:18:43,312 --> 00:18:44,854
[in English] Why're you protecting him?

355
00:18:45,687 --> 00:18:46,854
He left you.

356
00:18:46,937 --> 00:18:48,187
He drove off in your taxi.

357
00:18:48,271 --> 00:18:50,646
Where's your friends
when you need them, Kwanele?

358
00:18:54,562 --> 00:18:55,562
[in Sotho] Listen, man.

359
00:18:56,146 --> 00:18:57,687
[in English] It's not your fault.

360
00:18:57,771 --> 00:19:01,771
[in Sotho] In fact, a lot of people,
were telling us that…

361
00:19:01,854 --> 00:19:03,979
[in English] …you tried
to calm the situation down.

362
00:19:05,521 --> 00:19:07,521
[in Sotho] Right?
So I'm not looking for you.

363
00:19:08,562 --> 00:19:10,604
I'm looking for the guy
that was holding the gun.

364
00:19:11,271 --> 00:19:12,604
I want this guy.

365
00:19:17,771 --> 00:19:20,646
Kwanele, let's not bullshit
each other, you hear me?

366
00:19:22,354 --> 00:19:24,979
[stammers] I don't know of a gun.

367
00:19:25,062 --> 00:19:26,521
You don't know of a gun? Who's this?

368
00:19:27,146 --> 00:19:28,979
-Like I said, sir--
-[shouts] Who is he, man?

369
00:19:29,062 --> 00:19:30,312
I don't know him.

370
00:19:32,354 --> 00:19:34,062
I don't… don't know him, sir.

371
00:19:38,646 --> 00:19:39,896
May I please get a lawyer?

372
00:19:44,979 --> 00:19:46,396
[phone rings]

373
00:19:47,521 --> 00:19:49,271
[in English]
Hello, you're speaking to Grace.

374
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:51,604
To whom do I have
the pleasure of speaking to today?

375
00:19:51,687 --> 00:19:53,854
Listen, my son is in ICU.

376
00:19:53,937 --> 00:19:56,312
The hospital is telling me
that my medical aid has been suspended.

377
00:19:56,396 --> 00:19:57,396
[Grace] Very good, sir.

378
00:19:57,479 --> 00:20:00,812
This call is recorded
for quality and security purposes.

379
00:20:00,896 --> 00:20:03,312
Please confirm your address
and cell phone number.

380
00:20:03,396 --> 00:20:05,521
You have my cell phone number.
I'm calling from it right now!

381
00:20:05,604 --> 00:20:09,229
Yes, sir. But we need it
for our security protocol.

382
00:20:09,312 --> 00:20:11,729
069 777 8976.

383
00:20:11,812 --> 00:20:12,812
Thank you.

384
00:20:13,646 --> 00:20:15,021
You were saying, sir?

385
00:20:15,104 --> 00:20:17,062
[Zak] I'm saying that my son is in ICU!

386
00:20:17,146 --> 00:20:19,979
The hospital is telling me
that my medical aid has been suspended,

387
00:20:20,062 --> 00:20:22,479
and I will not let them take him
to a government hospital!

388
00:20:22,562 --> 00:20:24,812
Okay, let me just have a look quickly.

389
00:20:24,896 --> 00:20:28,271
[hold music playing on phone]

390
00:20:28,354 --> 00:20:30,312
Mr. Sigcawu?

391
00:20:30,396 --> 00:20:31,562
Yes.

392
00:20:31,646 --> 00:20:34,604
Uh, sir, could you stay on the line,
please, while I check your details?

393
00:20:34,687 --> 00:20:36,146
-[line beeps]
-No, I can…

394
00:20:37,021 --> 00:20:38,271
What the f…

395
00:20:38,354 --> 00:20:40,979
[hold music playing on phone]

396
00:20:43,104 --> 00:20:47,187
Um, Mr. Sigcawu, thank you very much
for staying on the line.

397
00:20:47,771 --> 00:20:50,521
Um, unfortunately, your…

398
00:20:51,104 --> 00:20:52,937
your stop order hasn't gone off
for two months.

399
00:20:53,021 --> 00:20:54,396
Listen to me. Listen to me.

400
00:20:54,479 --> 00:20:55,979
Grace, there must be a mistake.

401
00:20:56,062 --> 00:20:57,312
I do have the money.

402
00:20:57,396 --> 00:20:58,771
I just recently changed banks.

403
00:20:58,854 --> 00:21:03,562
Sir, if you can pay the outstanding amount
and, um, the hospital deposit…

404
00:21:03,646 --> 00:21:04,646
How much is that?

405
00:21:04,729 --> 00:21:05,854
Eighty thousand.

406
00:21:06,437 --> 00:21:08,812
-Listen, I'll have it here in 20 minutes.
-[keypad beeping]

407
00:21:09,979 --> 00:21:11,604
[phone rings]

408
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:13,604
-[Zak] Zuko.
-Hello.

409
00:21:13,687 --> 00:21:16,396
Listen to me. Just go to the safe
and bring me 80,000 rand.

410
00:21:16,479 --> 00:21:19,146
-[in Xhosa] Yeah. What happened now?
-[in English] Just bring me the money!

411
00:21:19,229 --> 00:21:20,979
And meet me at Mohlela Clinic, please.
Right now.

412
00:21:21,062 --> 00:21:22,312
[in Xhosa] Okay, I'm on it.

413
00:21:27,396 --> 00:21:29,187
[in English] He's a businessman.

414
00:21:29,271 --> 00:21:30,896
Owns a few burger franchises.

415
00:21:30,979 --> 00:21:32,312
Does he have a record?

416
00:21:33,146 --> 00:21:35,187
He and his brother
were arrested for assault.

417
00:21:36,021 --> 00:21:38,437
Sent a security guard to the hospital.

418
00:21:39,271 --> 00:21:40,271
And?

419
00:21:41,437 --> 00:21:43,354
I spoke to someone at Thokoza.

420
00:21:43,437 --> 00:21:46,521
They seem to think that Zak
was the problem, but Zuko took the rap.

421
00:21:46,604 --> 00:21:47,604
Got two years.

422
00:21:48,187 --> 00:21:49,354
Nice brother.

423
00:21:49,437 --> 00:21:50,521
[detective 1] Yeah.

424
00:21:51,146 --> 00:21:52,687
You'd take two years for me?

425
00:21:56,562 --> 00:21:57,562
Twenty years.

426
00:22:09,021 --> 00:22:10,937
[detective 1] We have the driver
in custody.

427
00:22:11,021 --> 00:22:12,646
Arrested at the crime scene.

428
00:22:15,021 --> 00:22:18,812
We'd like to see if you can identify
any other suspects.

429
00:22:21,187 --> 00:22:22,854
Take your time, Mr. Sigcawu.

430
00:22:23,812 --> 00:22:26,562
If you see someone that looks familiar,
just say their number.

431
00:22:39,729 --> 00:22:41,021
Can four please step forward?

432
00:22:41,104 --> 00:22:43,562
[detective 1] Number four,
step forward please.

433
00:22:45,812 --> 00:22:47,146
Turn to the side.

434
00:22:51,229 --> 00:22:52,354
The other side.

435
00:23:00,604 --> 00:23:02,437
Thank you. You can take your place.

436
00:23:13,146 --> 00:23:15,771
[tense music playing]

437
00:23:25,146 --> 00:23:27,146
Listen, I… I'm sorry.

438
00:23:31,396 --> 00:23:35,437
[Portia] ♪ Gentle Jesus, meek and mild ♪

439
00:23:36,896 --> 00:23:40,604
♪ Look upon your little child ♪

440
00:23:45,062 --> 00:23:48,562
♪ Hold me fast in thy embrace ♪

441
00:23:49,979 --> 00:23:53,687
♪ Let me see your smiling face ♪

442
00:23:58,062 --> 00:24:01,896
♪ Give me, Lord, thy blessings give ♪

443
00:24:06,396 --> 00:24:08,104
♪ Pray for me ♪

444
00:24:09,562 --> 00:24:11,771
♪ And I shall live ♪

445
00:24:24,687 --> 00:24:25,896
[sighs]

446
00:24:52,937 --> 00:24:55,354
You, with the shoes.

447
00:24:57,354 --> 00:24:58,354
It is you.

448
00:24:58,979 --> 00:25:00,312
[in Xhosa] You're the one
we're looking for?

449
00:25:00,396 --> 00:25:02,021
[in Tswana] I'm not your mother, get lost!

450
00:25:02,104 --> 00:25:03,854
[in Zulu] No, don't respond.
Don't respond.

451
00:25:04,396 --> 00:25:07,646
My client and I were leaving.
He has no charges.

452
00:25:07,729 --> 00:25:10,062
[in Xhosa] Listen here,
you're not going anywhere.

453
00:25:10,146 --> 00:25:12,062
Like I said,
this is the guy we're looking for.

454
00:25:12,146 --> 00:25:13,479
Who are you pointing at, dude?

455
00:25:13,562 --> 00:25:15,854
I'm pointing at you. What you gonna do
about it? This is who we're looking for.

456
00:25:15,937 --> 00:25:17,896
-You got your chance.
-What chance?

457
00:25:17,979 --> 00:25:20,021
[in English] Officer, this is the guy
we're looking for. Arrest him!

458
00:25:20,104 --> 00:25:22,646
-Stop staring at me, do your job!
-[detective 2] Hello.

459
00:25:22,729 --> 00:25:23,937
-[in English] What's going on?
-Detective.

460
00:25:24,021 --> 00:25:25,396
[in Xhosa] This is the person
we're searching for.

461
00:25:25,479 --> 00:25:27,729
[in English] He's the one
that kicked me in my face.

462
00:25:27,812 --> 00:25:30,146
-Are you sure?
-Of course I'm sure, so do your job.

463
00:25:30,229 --> 00:25:31,521
Well, let's go to my office.

464
00:25:31,604 --> 00:25:33,562
[in Xhosa] Office for what?
Here is the guy, he's right next to me.

465
00:25:33,646 --> 00:25:35,354
[shushing, in English]
Keep your voice down!

466
00:25:35,437 --> 00:25:37,812
-You didn't pick him out in the lineup.
-Don't tell me about lineups.

467
00:25:37,896 --> 00:25:39,896
I'm just telling you this is him
right here, in front of me!

468
00:25:39,979 --> 00:25:42,729
[detective 2] Listen to me.
There are processes.

469
00:25:42,812 --> 00:25:44,854
[in Xhosa] These people are leaving,
and you're letting them go. Can you see?

470
00:25:44,937 --> 00:25:46,729
[in English] You're not going to tell me
how to do my job.

471
00:25:46,812 --> 00:25:49,562
[in Xhosa] Do you not see what's going on?
Do your job, this person is leaving.

472
00:25:50,354 --> 00:25:52,146
-[people gasp]
-Hey, hey, hey!

473
00:25:52,854 --> 00:25:55,062
[in Zulu] All right, hey, sir, sir.

474
00:25:56,312 --> 00:25:57,729
[in Sotho] What do you want to do?

475
00:26:02,396 --> 00:26:03,729
Shoot!

476
00:26:05,312 --> 00:26:06,812
Shoot!

477
00:26:08,146 --> 00:26:09,437
Zakhele.

478
00:26:10,854 --> 00:26:11,937
[in English] This isn't helping.

479
00:26:14,229 --> 00:26:16,062
It's okay if you recognize him.

480
00:26:16,729 --> 00:26:20,479
We can put it on our records
as an accidental identification.

481
00:26:20,562 --> 00:26:21,562
Still holds up.

482
00:26:23,687 --> 00:26:24,687
Move!

483
00:26:28,396 --> 00:26:29,854
[detective 1] Your wife needs you.

484
00:26:32,729 --> 00:26:34,937
Your son needs you.

485
00:26:36,479 --> 00:26:37,687
Put the gun down.

486
00:26:38,479 --> 00:26:40,104
We'll make this all go away.

487
00:26:56,479 --> 00:26:59,854
[rapid beeping]

488
00:27:17,271 --> 00:27:20,229
[steady beep]

489
00:27:28,229 --> 00:27:29,437
[defibrillator charging]

490
00:27:29,521 --> 00:27:31,021
No, wait!

491
00:27:32,104 --> 00:27:34,062
Oh, my gosh. Mandla, please.

492
00:27:36,896 --> 00:27:38,646
God, please. Please, God, no.

493
00:27:38,729 --> 00:27:40,146
No, no, no, please.

494
00:27:41,687 --> 00:27:43,229
-Oh, God.
-[defibrillator thuds]

495
00:27:43,312 --> 00:27:45,312
Oh, my God. Please.

496
00:27:48,271 --> 00:27:49,437
Oh, my God.

497
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:56,812
[mournful music plays]

