Yes, press that button.

753
00:52:01,396 --> 00:52:04,896
It's not a train smash, you can report it.

754
00:52:04,979 --> 00:52:06,562
I love you, too.

755
00:52:07,354 --> 00:52:08,937
I love you more.

756
00:52:09,729 --> 00:52:10,854
[in Afrikaans] It's true.

757
00:52:14,854 --> 00:52:17,312
[in English] You don't fucking move.
[in Zulu] You hear me?

758
00:52:18,312 --> 00:52:19,646
[in English] You killed my son…

759
00:52:20,271 --> 00:52:21,396
[in Zulu] …you dog.

760
00:52:22,646 --> 00:52:24,312
[in Xhosa] You're next, do you hear me?

761
00:52:26,021 --> 00:52:27,562
[in Tswana] If you were going to kill me,

762
00:52:28,479 --> 00:52:30,021
I'd be dead already.

763
00:52:35,771 --> 00:52:37,562
-Go.
-Where you taking me?

764
00:52:37,646 --> 00:52:39,104
To the police. I said go.

765
00:52:39,187 --> 00:52:40,604
[Lerumo laughs]

766
00:52:44,354 --> 00:52:46,062
You're so stupid, you know.

767
00:52:46,812 --> 00:52:48,937
You're lucky you killed Shoes.

768
00:52:49,437 --> 00:52:54,979
Shooting someone in the face
for the first time is no child's play.

769
00:52:55,062 --> 00:52:57,604
Shoot me in my head.

770
00:52:59,062 --> 00:53:00,271
Shoot, man!

771
00:53:01,354 --> 00:53:02,521
Shoot, man!

772
00:53:04,271 --> 00:53:06,437
Don't drive me crazy, I said shoot.

773
00:53:07,812 --> 00:53:09,687
[door opens, closes]

774
00:53:14,521 --> 00:53:16,312
[in Zulu] Goodness, Zuko, what happened?

775
00:53:16,396 --> 00:53:17,729
[in Xhosa] I got shot.

776
00:53:17,812 --> 00:53:19,021
[in Zulu] Who shot you?

777
00:53:21,271 --> 00:53:22,354
Zak.

778
00:53:22,437 --> 00:53:24,062
[in Xhosa] It's that uncontrollable
temper of his.

779
00:53:24,146 --> 00:53:25,312
Zuko.

780
00:53:25,396 --> 00:53:27,479
I know, I know, it was a mistake.

781
00:53:27,562 --> 00:53:29,937
He didn't mean to. He wanted his gun,
and I took it away from him.

782
00:53:30,687 --> 00:53:31,937
-Where is he?
-I don't know.

783
00:53:32,021 --> 00:53:33,562
I thought you would know
where he might be.

784
00:53:33,646 --> 00:53:35,354
No, I'm trying to get ahold of him.
I don't know where he is.

785
00:53:38,687 --> 00:53:40,104
I thought he was here.

786
00:53:41,021 --> 00:53:42,229
Where is he?

787
00:53:57,521 --> 00:53:59,229
[in English] Zuko, did he kill that guy?

788
00:54:15,229 --> 00:54:16,771
[detective, on phone] Detective Titus.

789
00:54:16,854 --> 00:54:18,229
Hi, Detective.

790
00:54:19,396 --> 00:54:21,396
-This is Mrs. Sigcawu.
-Yes.

791
00:54:22,562 --> 00:54:24,187
I think my husband's in danger.

792
00:54:26,979 --> 00:54:29,729
[Eezy, in Sotho] The problem
with marrying a wife with a flat chest

793
00:54:29,812 --> 00:54:31,937
is that they don't feed.

794
00:54:32,604 --> 00:54:34,854
[in English] Eh? Nothing to suck on.

795
00:54:42,479 --> 00:54:44,312
You remind me of a little dog.

796
00:54:44,396 --> 00:54:47,354
A Chihuahua that ventured
into the wrong doghouse

797
00:54:47,437 --> 00:54:49,021
looking for a bone to chew on.

798
00:54:50,479 --> 00:54:54,687
Little did it know,
that inside there is the big dog.

799
00:54:55,396 --> 00:54:56,479
Bulldog.

800
00:54:56,562 --> 00:54:57,604
[in Xhosa] A wild dog.

801
00:54:58,396 --> 00:55:00,562
[in English] You see those cars outside?

802
00:55:01,437 --> 00:55:02,854
Those are not cars.

803
00:55:02,937 --> 00:55:04,146
They're coffins.

804
00:55:04,729 --> 00:55:06,187
This is the graveside.

805
00:55:07,021 --> 00:55:11,521
You don't walk into this doghouse
like a hunting dog, with a gun in hand,

806
00:55:11,604 --> 00:55:13,229
and walk out alive.

807
00:55:13,312 --> 00:55:14,646
This is my domain!

808
00:55:14,729 --> 00:55:18,521
I am God. I am Satan, the butcher.

809
00:55:21,312 --> 00:55:22,937
You're going to die, Son.

810
00:55:25,021 --> 00:55:28,604
The most horrific violation
you will ever see.

811
00:55:30,271 --> 00:55:31,896
But that's the easy part.

812
00:55:32,646 --> 00:55:35,479
The fun part is knowing
how you're going to die,

813
00:55:35,562 --> 00:55:37,937
so keep your eyes open.

814
00:55:41,187 --> 00:55:42,187
Take him.

815
00:55:45,979 --> 00:55:48,729
[in Tswana] On top of everything, boss,
he's gonna go out with piles.

816
00:55:49,437 --> 00:55:52,562
Fenya, help me carry this rubbish.
Let's go.

817
00:55:52,646 --> 00:55:54,521
-He's heavy.
-[Fenya] Hold the legs.

818
00:55:54,604 --> 00:55:56,437
[Lerumo] Hold the legs?
This person is big.

819
00:55:56,521 --> 00:55:59,271
You can tell he's always in the gym.

820
00:56:00,396 --> 00:56:03,187
-[Fenya] Let me open this.
-[Lerumo] Okay, okay.

821
00:56:03,271 --> 00:56:06,187
[in Sepedi] I want to show this boy
something. Pick up my goggles.

822
00:56:07,271 --> 00:56:08,479
Piss off!

823
00:56:09,521 --> 00:56:12,187
[Lerumo] I want to show him…
I want to show him something.

824
00:56:14,521 --> 00:56:15,937
[engine starts]

825
00:56:17,229 --> 00:56:19,437
[equipment whirring]

826
00:56:33,271 --> 00:56:35,229
[rumbling]

827
00:56:35,312 --> 00:56:37,062
[clanking]

828
00:56:59,354 --> 00:57:02,062
[breathing heavily]

829
00:57:06,312 --> 00:57:08,312
[banging]

830
00:57:09,062 --> 00:57:10,771
Hey. Hey!

831
00:57:11,479 --> 00:57:12,687
Hey!

832
00:57:13,562 --> 00:57:14,562
No!

833
00:57:16,062 --> 00:57:17,062
Hey!

834
00:57:18,187 --> 00:57:19,229
Hey!

835
00:57:23,354 --> 00:57:24,354
No!

836
00:57:25,896 --> 00:57:26,896
Hey!

837
00:57:27,562 --> 00:57:30,229
[siren wailing]

838
00:57:44,521 --> 00:57:46,229
Gents, go!

839
00:57:51,896 --> 00:57:53,271
[in English] May I help you?

840
00:57:53,354 --> 00:57:56,187
We have reason to believe
that Zakhele Sigcawu is on your premises.

841
00:57:56,854 --> 00:57:57,854
Who?

842
00:57:58,771 --> 00:58:00,271
The man who lost his son.

843
00:58:01,312 --> 00:58:02,437
He's looking for him here?

844
00:58:03,312 --> 00:58:06,271
[in Sotho] Mr. Rampedi, we're not here
to play hide-and-seek, sir.

845
00:58:07,021 --> 00:58:08,312
[in English] Do you have a warrant?

846
00:58:08,396 --> 00:58:09,562
We don't need one.

847
00:58:34,312 --> 00:58:35,729
[grunting]

848
00:58:54,062 --> 00:58:55,271
[sighs]

849
00:59:02,021 --> 00:59:03,396
Shit!

850
00:59:46,146 --> 00:59:47,479
[Layla] You find something?

851
00:59:50,896 --> 00:59:52,021
No.

852
00:59:55,854 --> 00:59:57,104
Are you guys done?

853
01:00:14,437 --> 01:00:15,687
-[Eezy, in Tswana] Hey, Lerumo.
-Yes.

854
01:00:15,771 --> 01:00:17,854
-[Eezy] Did you find him?
-No, boss.

855
01:00:17,937 --> 01:00:19,271
[Eezy] Here, take this.

856
01:00:20,271 --> 01:00:21,521
[in Sotho] This is his address.

857
01:00:22,104 --> 01:00:25,646
Kill each and everything
you find in his house.

858
01:00:25,729 --> 01:00:29,937
Dog, cat, woman, kill anything.
You hear me?

859
01:00:30,021 --> 01:00:31,687
-[Lerumo] I'm on top of it, boss.
-Go with Karwas.

860
01:00:31,771 --> 01:00:33,146
[Lerumo] Let's go. Let's go, guys.

861
01:00:33,229 --> 01:00:35,354
-Go, Karwas, man.
-Why are you still dragging your feet?

862
01:00:35,437 --> 01:00:36,521
[Fenya] This guy.

863
01:00:37,396 --> 01:00:38,812
[Eezy] How did you lose that boy?

864
01:01:19,604 --> 01:01:21,021
[snoring]

865
01:01:22,062 --> 01:01:23,271
[door opens gently]

866
01:01:38,604 --> 01:01:39,687
[snoring]

867
01:01:39,771 --> 01:01:40,896
[clattering]

868
01:02:13,937 --> 01:02:15,604
And what are you two doing
in my brother's house?

869
01:02:15,687 --> 01:02:16,771
[grunts]

870
01:02:18,229 --> 01:02:20,854
[Lerumo] Let's go, let's go.

871
01:02:20,937 --> 01:02:22,021
[Karwas] I'm coming, I'm coming.

872
01:02:22,104 --> 01:02:24,187
-[Lerumo] Why are you startled?
-[Karwas] No.

873
01:02:24,271 --> 01:02:26,021
-[Lerumo] Are you wearing an underskirt?
-[Karwas] Mm-mmm.

874
01:02:26,104 --> 01:02:28,312
-[Lerumo] Let's go, let's go.
-I'm not wearing an underskirt.

875
01:02:39,437 --> 01:02:41,062
[in Tswana] Check the bedroom, my friend.

876
01:02:57,187 --> 01:02:58,937
[breathing shakily]

877
01:03:03,271 --> 01:03:04,396
Zuko…

878
01:03:07,062 --> 01:03:08,062
Zuko.

879
01:03:08,854 --> 01:03:11,437
-[sobbing]
-[muttering]

880
01:03:12,521 --> 01:03:13,562
No…

881
01:03:16,229 --> 01:03:17,229
Oh, no.

882
01:03:20,146 --> 01:03:22,562
[Lerumo, in Tswana]
Karwas, I'm going downstairs.

883
01:03:55,187 --> 01:03:56,187
Zak.

884
01:03:57,062 --> 01:03:58,979
[in English] Come on. They're inside.

885
01:04:05,396 --> 01:04:07,229
-Mm, mm, mm.
-[fork clatters]

886
01:04:17,562 --> 01:04:19,062
[Portia, softly] Zak. Oh, God.

887
01:04:27,812 --> 01:04:29,187
[Lerumo, in Afrikaans] Hey.

888
01:04:29,271 --> 01:04:30,562
[Karwas] Yes?

889
01:04:30,646 --> 01:04:31,896
See anything?

890
01:04:33,562 --> 01:04:35,729
Uh, nothing.

891
01:04:38,729 --> 01:04:39,896
[container clatters]

892
01:04:46,021 --> 01:04:47,729
The boss won't be happy.

893
01:05:03,021 --> 01:05:04,062
Zuko.

894
01:05:05,646 --> 01:05:06,729
Zuko.

895
01:05:09,562 --> 01:05:10,854
[in English] Zuko, come on, man.

896
01:05:31,437 --> 01:05:32,771
[Portia] You need to stop this.

897
01:05:42,937 --> 01:05:44,146
Me?

898
01:05:48,979 --> 01:05:50,437
Zakhele, look around.

899
01:05:51,979 --> 01:05:53,062
Your son,

900
01:05:54,062 --> 01:05:55,187
your brother.

901
01:05:59,146 --> 01:06:00,854
You just never know when to stop.

902
01:06:03,229 --> 01:06:04,562
You need to tell the police.

903
01:06:07,146 --> 01:06:08,146
The police?

904
01:06:08,229 --> 01:06:09,854
[in Xhosa] He works for them.
If I don't do this--

905
01:06:09,937 --> 01:06:12,354
[in English] Zakhele,
you're gonna get yourself killed.

906
01:06:12,437 --> 01:06:14,479
-I don't care.
-I do.

907
01:06:16,771 --> 01:06:19,271
-Portia, if I don't do this--
-I need you.

908
01:06:22,729 --> 01:06:24,229
I can't lose you too.

909
01:06:32,479 --> 01:06:34,937
[siren wailing in distance]

910
01:06:58,979 --> 01:07:01,812
[siren continues]

911
01:07:48,146 --> 01:07:49,562
[phone buzzing]

912
01:08:06,854 --> 01:08:09,396
-Hello?
-[Grace] Mr. Sigcawu?

913
01:08:09,479 --> 01:08:12,854
At last. I…
I hope it's not too late to call you.

914
01:08:12,937 --> 01:08:16,521
I… I've been trying to get a hold of you
for the past couple of days.

915
01:08:16,604 --> 01:08:18,229
I've got such great news.

916
01:08:18,312 --> 01:08:20,687
I spoke to my supervisor and…

917
01:08:21,729 --> 01:08:24,062
we have agreed to void your arrears.

918
01:08:24,146 --> 01:08:28,687
Plus, you've been selected
for the new gold status credit card.

919
01:08:28,771 --> 01:08:30,104
-Really?
-[Grace] Yes, yes.

920
01:08:30,187 --> 01:08:32,021
Um, just one thing.

921
01:08:32,104 --> 01:08:36,187
There is a claim for, um, your son Mandla.

922
01:08:36,271 --> 01:08:38,521
The hospital plan
won't be able to cover it,

923
01:08:38,604 --> 01:08:41,562
because it wasn't an overnight stay.

924
01:08:42,229 --> 01:08:43,229
My son…

925
01:08:44,979 --> 01:08:46,104
Mandla.

926
01:08:47,396 --> 01:08:48,937
He's still there.

927
01:08:49,021 --> 01:08:51,396
Really? Um, our records don't show that.

928
01:08:51,479 --> 01:08:52,771
Let me just…

929
01:08:54,354 --> 01:08:55,729
They did a postmortem.

930
01:08:57,354 --> 01:08:58,354
[sighs]

931
01:08:59,271 --> 01:09:01,229
Oh, my word. I'm so sorry.

932
01:09:04,562 --> 01:09:06,396
I'm so sorry, I…

933
01:09:06,479 --> 01:09:09,937
I'm so sorry to have called you now,
and I'm so sorry for your loss.

934
01:09:10,646 --> 01:09:12,729
But you were giving me a credit card.

935
01:09:12,812 --> 01:09:14,521
Oh, my God.

936
01:09:15,604 --> 01:09:16,604
[sniffles]

937
01:09:17,771 --> 01:09:18,771
[sighs]

938
01:09:23,354 --> 01:09:24,479
I, um…

939
01:09:26,729 --> 01:09:28,104
I lost a child too.

940
01:09:29,771 --> 01:09:31,187
[Grace crying]

941
01:09:32,937 --> 01:09:34,937
There isn't a day that goes by…

942
01:09:36,521 --> 01:09:39,021
that I don't talk to her.

943
01:09:43,771 --> 01:09:45,479
What did you say your name was?

944
01:09:50,271 --> 01:09:51,562
It's Grace.

945
01:09:54,687 --> 01:09:56,229
Your mother named you well.

946
01:10:00,646 --> 01:10:03,812
[in Zulu] ♪ My beautiful home ♪

947
01:10:03,896 --> 01:10:09,146
♪ My home ♪

948
01:10:09,229 --> 01:10:16,229
♪ Let me enter the gate ♪

949
01:10:16,312 --> 01:10:18,521
♪ Let me rest ♪

950
01:10:18,604 --> 01:10:25,604
♪ Let me rest in you ♪

951
01:10:25,687 --> 01:10:28,229
♪ My beautiful home ♪

952
01:10:28,312 --> 01:10:30,312
♪ My beautiful home ♪

953
01:10:30,396 --> 01:10:31,812
♪ My home ♪

954
01:10:31,896 --> 01:10:36,687
♪ My home ♪

955
01:10:41,396 --> 01:10:42,729
Be strong, okay?

956
01:10:54,021 --> 01:10:56,229
[in English] It should have been
my son's job to give my eulogy,

957
01:10:56,312 --> 01:10:57,729
not mine to give his.

958
01:11:02,729 --> 01:11:04,104
What do you say about a…

959
01:11:06,062 --> 01:11:08,187
seven-year-old boy who…

960
01:11:11,021 --> 01:11:12,729
loved dinosaurs…

961
01:11:14,479 --> 01:11:15,854
and the night sky.

962
01:11:17,646 --> 01:11:19,312
Who'd ask questions like,

963
01:11:19,396 --> 01:11:24,604
"What language do cats and dogs use
when they talk to each other?"

964
01:11:29,479 --> 01:11:31,896
Would talk to his toys as if…

965
01:11:32,646 --> 01:11:34,437
as if they were real.

966
01:11:37,146 --> 01:11:38,854
And who, when asked…

967
01:11:40,521 --> 01:11:42,146
by his teacher what…

968
01:11:46,062 --> 01:11:48,312
what he wanted to be when he grew up…

969
01:11:54,562 --> 01:11:55,979
said, "Kind."

970
01:12:29,271 --> 01:12:31,104
[panting]

971
01:12:39,604 --> 01:12:44,437
[in Zulu] ♪ Even when ♪

972
01:12:46,271 --> 01:12:51,771
♪ I'm afflicted, Lord ♪

973
01:12:52,687 --> 01:12:56,854
♪ When I'm sleeping on a rock ♪

974
01:12:58,146 --> 01:13:00,771
♪ And experiencing hardships ♪

975
01:13:00,854 --> 01:13:02,062
♪ Lord ♪

976
01:13:05,896 --> 01:13:07,937
[panting]

977
01:13:34,021 --> 01:13:35,021
[in English] Fuck!

978
01:13:44,562 --> 01:13:46,187
[Portia sobbing]

979
01:13:48,104 --> 01:13:49,562
[Ma, in Afrikaans] I'm sorry.

980
01:13:51,937 --> 01:13:53,146
Sorry.

981
01:14:04,812 --> 01:14:06,104
[engine starts]

982
01:14:07,271 --> 01:14:09,979
[in English] Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Hey, hey, hey!

983
01:14:10,729 --> 01:14:13,062
Hey! Hey, hey, hey, Zak!

984
01:14:14,146 --> 01:14:15,187
Fuck!

985
01:14:20,021 --> 01:14:21,021
[phone buzzes]

986
01:14:22,604 --> 01:14:25,187
[Floyd, in Sotho] Dude, this guy is crazy.
He's on his way to you.

987
01:14:25,271 --> 01:14:28,271
[hip-hop music playing]

988
01:15:07,729 --> 01:15:09,437
[horn honks]

989
01:15:11,521 --> 01:15:13,312
[in English]
Delivery for Mr. Ezekiel Rampedi.

990
01:15:13,396 --> 01:15:15,021
[guard, in Xhosa] I'll take it, Brother.

991
01:15:15,104 --> 01:15:18,062
[Zak] I won't be able to log it
into my app.

992
01:15:24,687 --> 01:15:26,646
-[Eezy] Lerumo.
-Yes.

993
01:15:27,687 --> 01:15:29,687
[Eezy] Tell these boys,
Hammer and Spyker,

994
01:15:30,312 --> 01:15:33,479
if they don't kill that Chihuahua
by the end of this week,

995
01:15:34,187 --> 01:15:36,937
-I'm going to kill them.
-[Lerumo] Okay, I'll let them know, boss.

996
01:15:37,771 --> 01:15:38,771
Sure thing.

997
01:15:38,854 --> 01:15:40,187
-[Eezy] Good.
-[Lerumo] Sure.

998
01:15:52,437 --> 01:15:53,687
-[object clatters]
-[gasps]

999
01:16:49,396 --> 01:16:51,812
[both grunting]

1000
01:17:17,062 --> 01:17:18,854
[Lerumo screams]

1001
01:17:19,937 --> 01:17:21,437
[in English] Fuck! Fuck!

1002
01:17:24,229 --> 01:17:25,521
Fuck!

1003
01:17:25,604 --> 01:17:26,896
[groans]

1004
01:17:35,937 --> 01:17:37,271
What the fuck?

1005
01:17:40,229 --> 01:17:41,437
[in Tswana] I'm going to find you.

1006
01:17:42,854 --> 01:17:44,812
And then I'm going to pull your teeth out.

1007
01:17:45,479 --> 01:17:47,604
[in English] One by one.

1008
01:17:48,646 --> 01:17:50,396
[in Tswana]
Then I'm going to feed them to you.

1009
01:17:51,146 --> 01:17:52,604
And you'll swallow them.

1010
01:17:54,437 --> 01:17:56,396
I'm going to kill you, boy.

1011
01:17:57,896 --> 01:17:59,771
Then I'm going to bring you back to life.

1012
01:18:01,646 --> 01:18:03,062
So I can kill you…

1013
01:18:04,437 --> 01:18:05,437
again.

1014
01:18:06,229 --> 01:18:07,479
And again.

1015
01:18:08,479 --> 01:18:09,687
And again.

1016
01:18:11,479 --> 01:18:13,104
[in Sepedi] Come here, bastard.

1017
01:18:15,021 --> 01:18:17,021
[groans]

1018
01:18:17,104 --> 01:18:19,521
Hey, man!
You want me to show you your mother?

1019
01:18:19,604 --> 01:18:22,021
I can't see! I can't see anything!

1020
01:18:22,104 --> 01:18:23,896
When I catch you, I'll…

1021
01:18:26,396 --> 01:18:27,562
[gasps]

1022
01:18:40,687 --> 01:18:42,729
[chuckling]

1023
01:18:47,771 --> 01:18:49,437
[in Xhosa] What's so funny, you rubbish?

1024
01:18:49,521 --> 01:18:51,896
[Lerumo, in Tswana]
You still think you're all that.

1025
01:18:52,521 --> 01:18:53,521
You bird.

1026
01:18:56,437 --> 01:18:57,729
[in English] You killed my son.

1027
01:18:58,479 --> 01:18:59,854
[in Tswana] You're such an idiot.

1028
01:19:01,521 --> 01:19:02,854
It was Karwas.

1029
01:19:03,521 --> 01:19:05,437
He grabbed the gun and pulled the trigger.

1030
01:19:05,521 --> 01:19:08,854
[in English] But it was you,
father of the year.

1031
01:19:08,937 --> 01:19:11,187
You killed your son.

1032
01:19:11,271 --> 01:19:12,646
[in Xhosa] Stop lying!

1033
01:19:14,687 --> 01:19:16,979
[blood dripping]

1034
01:19:21,396 --> 01:19:22,979
[in English] Dead men don't lie.

1035
01:19:24,937 --> 01:19:26,646
[choking]

1036
01:19:36,396 --> 01:19:38,396
[dogs barking]

1037
01:19:49,354 --> 01:19:50,479
Lerumo!

1038
01:19:52,812 --> 01:19:54,062
[in Xhosa] Drop your gun.

1039
01:19:55,479 --> 01:19:57,604
-[in English] Drop the fucking gun!
-Sure, sure, sure.

1040
01:19:59,396 --> 01:20:01,021
[in Xhosa] Don't shoot me.

1041
01:20:01,104 --> 01:20:02,687
Don't shoot me, boy.

1042
01:20:04,312 --> 01:20:05,729
Where's Karwas?

1043
01:20:05,812 --> 01:20:08,271
Look, I'll tell you everything
that you want to know.

1044
01:20:08,354 --> 01:20:09,646
But don't shoot me.

1045
01:20:09,729 --> 01:20:11,021
Where is Karwas?

1046
01:20:11,104 --> 01:20:13,979
He's at 31-37 at T Marshall.

1047
01:20:16,021 --> 01:20:18,187
[in English] Zakhele, drop your weapon.

1048
01:20:19,979 --> 01:20:21,437
[Floyd, in Xhosa] Drop the gun, man.

1049
01:20:21,521 --> 01:20:22,896
[in Sotho] Shoot him!

1050
01:20:23,854 --> 01:20:25,354
[in English] Zakhele, don't do this.

1051
01:20:26,854 --> 01:20:28,896
[in Sotho] Shoot this devil, man.

1052
01:20:28,979 --> 01:20:30,604
[in Xhosa] Drop the gun, Zakhele!

1053
01:20:31,271 --> 01:20:32,771
[in English] What do I pay you for?

1054
01:20:36,104 --> 01:20:37,562
[grunts, groans]

1055
01:20:42,229 --> 01:20:45,354
[engine starts, revs]

1056
01:20:53,146 --> 01:20:54,187
[gun cocks]

1057
01:21:02,104 --> 01:21:03,312
It was you.

1058
01:21:06,354 --> 01:21:08,646
Layla, put your gun down
before you hurt someone.

1059
01:21:09,354 --> 01:21:10,937
How could you?

1060
01:21:22,021 --> 01:21:23,021
Layla…

1061
01:21:27,312 --> 01:21:28,312
Layla.

1062
01:21:32,437 --> 01:21:33,687
[groans]

1063
01:21:34,854 --> 01:21:35,854
Fuck.

1064
01:21:35,937 --> 01:21:37,062
[body thuds]

1065
01:22:26,187 --> 01:22:28,104
[grunting]

1066
01:22:45,062 --> 01:22:47,437
[in Tswana] It was a mistake.

1067
01:22:48,562 --> 01:22:50,187
I never meant to kill him.

1068
01:22:53,021 --> 01:22:54,437
It was a mistake.

1069
01:22:55,021 --> 01:22:57,187
[in Afrikaans] I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1070
01:22:57,979 --> 01:22:59,104
[in Zulu] Dad.

1071
01:23:00,646 --> 01:23:02,479
[Karwas screams]

1072
01:23:04,021 --> 01:23:06,104
[groaning]

1073
01:23:12,937 --> 01:23:14,396
-Mandla?
-Dad.

1074
01:23:16,187 --> 01:23:17,187
Mandla.

1075
01:23:19,271 --> 01:23:20,271
Mandla.

1076
01:23:20,896 --> 01:23:21,896
My boy.

1077
01:23:30,396 --> 01:23:32,104
It's okay, Dad.

1078
01:23:39,771 --> 01:23:41,062
I love you, Dad.

1079
01:23:44,771 --> 01:23:46,104
I love you too, my boy.

1080
01:23:58,396 --> 01:23:59,479
Daddy loves you.

1081
01:24:08,021 --> 01:24:10,021
[Karwas, in Tswana]
Tsatsi! Tsatsi! Tsatsi, wait.

1082
01:24:10,104 --> 01:24:12,187
Tsatsi! Tsatsi! Letsatsi!

1083
01:24:12,271 --> 01:24:14,646
Don't do that. I'm begging you, boy.

1084
01:24:14,729 --> 01:24:17,354
Please, my boy, put the gun down.

1085
01:24:18,562 --> 01:24:19,687
Listen to me.

1086
01:24:21,062 --> 01:24:22,229
Put the gun down.

1087
01:24:22,312 --> 01:24:24,854
Put the gun down please, Tsatsi.

1088
01:24:24,937 --> 01:24:26,146
Tsatsi.

1089
01:24:30,229 --> 01:24:31,937
Come here. Come here, boy.

1090
01:24:32,021 --> 01:24:33,354
Come here, my boy.

1091
01:25:36,521 --> 01:25:37,771
[line ringing]

1092
01:25:38,562 --> 01:25:39,729
Hello?

1093
01:25:42,229 --> 01:25:43,229
[Zak] Grace.

1094
01:25:43,979 --> 01:25:46,729
Mr. Sigcawu, what can I do for you?

1095
01:25:47,479 --> 01:25:49,104
Listen, I need an ambulance.

1096
01:25:49,187 --> 01:25:51,104
I'll send you the location right now.

1097
01:25:51,812 --> 01:25:52,812
Are you okay?

1098
01:25:54,229 --> 01:25:55,229
[Zak] Yes.

1099
01:25:56,021 --> 01:25:57,021
Okay.

1100
01:26:22,271 --> 01:26:24,104
[thunder rumbling]

1101
01:26:27,521 --> 01:26:29,729
[Zak, in Xhosa] I know you don't want
to talk to me right now.

1102
01:26:31,771 --> 01:26:34,896
If I knew better,
I would've never gotten out of that car.

1103
01:26:36,062 --> 01:26:39,771
And Mandla would've still been alive.

1104
01:26:42,521 --> 01:26:44,396
I should've listened to you, my love.

1105
01:26:46,229 --> 01:26:48,646
[somber music playing]

1106
01:27:59,896 --> 01:28:01,396
[driver] Where are you going, man?

